Either youve updated the rio to the 2023 image but are running 2022 wpilib, or youve updated your code to 2023 wpilib and haven’t reimaged the rio to 2023.

The solution is to do whichever you havent done yet.

If you look closely at the image, it says:

Current image version: 2023_v3.1
GradleRIO-compatible image version: 2022_v4.*

Roborio is in the 2023 version, but GradleRIO is not. Install/update WPILib 2023, then from the 2023 version of VSCode open the project. It will ask you to import it to 2023 version, and you may have to re-install some vendordeps. Once this is done, it should work.
